gomodel:SYNGO_921  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: To study the role of PLC gamma1, the authors created a conditional knockout (Plcg1 f/f) and crossed it with Camk II-Cre to knockout the gene specifically in forebrain. The resulting mouse is named Plcg1 ff:Camk II throughout the article.\n\nAt the Schaffer collateral, no differences were observed in basal synaptic transmission (Figure 3A), but theta-burst induced LTP, and BDNF-induced potentiation were abolished (figure 3B, C). It should be noted that LTP induced by high frequency stimulation, which according to the authors is BDNF-independent, is not affected (supplemental figure 7). It is concluded that PLC gamma1 acts downstream of TrkB in BNDF-dependent forms of LTP.. Experimental description: Mice\nCaMKII-Cre\n15\nand\nNestin-Cre\n16\nmice were obtained from the Jackson\nLaboratory (Bar Harbor, ME, USA) and housed under a 12- h light\n-\ndark\ncycle and given access to food and water\nad libitum\n. Only male mice were\nused for physiological and behavioral analyses. All procedures were\napproved by the Institutional Animal Care and Utilization Committee of\nPOSTECH and conducted in accordance with the UNIST Guide for the Care\nand Use of Laboratory Animals (UNISTIACUC-14-005)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_921" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

